One python source file corresponds to one question:
a) rbm.py
b) rbm_k.py
c) rbm_sample.py
d) rbm_pretrain.py
e) autoencoder.py
f) denoising_autoencoder.py
g)

To check one specific question, just run the corresponding file. The code will output images to local disks, and print some info like entropy and error rate.